--band      : Tabulate energy bands; see doc/Command-line-options.html
--bonly     : Use in conjuction with --lxb switch
--chimedit    : Invoke magnetic susceptibility editor
--chklim    : Check band limits in optics calculations
--cls       : For core-level spectroscopy
--cv:       : Calculate electronic specific heat, eV
--cvK:      : Calculate electronic specific heat, Ry
--dos       : Calculate total DOS, and qualifying switches
--dumprho   : Not documented
--etot      : 1-shot total energy mode.  No forces, dynamics, output density
--evec      : Writes eigenvectors to disk
--invbl     : Not documented
--jdosw     : Channels for optical properties; See doc/optics.html
--jdosw2    : Channels for optical properties; See doc/optics.html
--lxb       : Write optical matrix elements for LXB code
--mem       : Use disk to conserve memory
--mix=      : Not documented
--mixsig=   : For self-energy; see Command-line-options.html
--mlog      : (MPI) write MPI commands to log file
--mull      : Mulliken analysis; see doc/Command-line-options.html
--no-fixef0 : Do not adjust estimate of Fermi level after 1st band pass
--nosymdm   : Not documented
--oldbz     : Not documented
--oldvc     : Reference potential defined so average cell potential is zero
--onesp     : Generate bands for one spin.  Better: use --band~spin1...
--opt:read  : Read optical matrix elements; See doc/optics.html
--opt:write : Write optical matrix elements; See doc/optics.html
--optbas    : Special branch to optimise basis
--pdiag     : (MPI) parallel diagonaliser
--pdos      : Partial DOS; see doc/Command-line-options.html
--popted    : Invoke the optics editor
--quit=     : quit after execution of certain blocks, e.g. --quit=ham
--rhopos    : force interstitial density to be every postive
--rs=       : Controls I/O with rst file; see Command-line-options.html
--rsedit    : Invoke the restart file editor
--rsig      : For reading the self-energy; see Command-line-options.html
--rxes      : RXES spectroscopy
--sh=       : Not documented
--shorps    : Shorten basis vectors after final input (e.g. from iors)
--shorten=no: Suppress all shortening of basis vectors
--vext      : Add external potential
--wden      : Write density to file
--wforce    : Write forces to file
--window=   : Generate output density in a restricted energy window
--wpotmt    : Write augmentation potentials to atom files
--wrhoat    : Write partial atomic densities to atom files
--wrhomt    : Write augmentation densities to files
--wsig      : For writing the self-energy; see Command-line-options.html
--wsmpot    : Write smooth potential to file
-ef=        : Overwrite Fermi level; use with --band
-enu=       : Not documented
-noves      : Use Madelung potential from disk; do not remake from density
-novintr    : Exclude intra-atomic W when making screened exchange sigma
--udrs      : generate and save output density
